.\" $Id$
.\" The following macro turns the program name in uppercase letters.
.de uppercase
.  tr aAbBcCdDeEfFgGhHiIjJkKlLmMnNoOpPqQrRsStTuUvVwWxXyYzZ
.  di uppercase
.    nop \\*[\\$1]
.    br
.  di
.  asciify uppercase
.  chop uppercase
.  tr aabbccddeeffgghhiijjkkllmmnnooppqqrrssttuuvvwwxxyyzz
.  ds \\$2 \\*[uppercase]\"
..
.\" Define the program name in its original and uppercase forms.
.ds name gchem3d@STABILITY@
.uppercase name NAME
.de prog
.  B gchem3d@STABILITY@
..
.\" Begin manual page.
.TH "\*[NAME]" "1" "@GCU_API_VER@" "gnome-chemistry-utils @VERSION@" "User commands"

.SH "NAME"
\*[name] \- a small chemical viewer application

.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.prog
.B [options]
.BI [ file ]

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
.prog
is a small chemical viewer application, which can show several chemical file
formats.

.SH "OPTIONS"
.PP
The following options are accepted:

.TP
\fB\-b \fICOLOR\fR, \fB\-\-bgcolor=\fICOLOR\fR
Use the given color as background color. \fICOLOR\fR can be one
of "\fIblack\fR" (default), "\fIwhite\fR" and "\fI#rrggbb\fR".
Dont forget to escape the "#" character in the shell).

.TP
\fB\-d \fIMODEL\fR, \fB\-\-display3d=\fIMODEL\fR
Choose how molecules are displayed. \fIMODEL\fR can be one
of "\fIBallnStick\fR" (default) and "\fISpaceFill\fR".

.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help ", " \-\-help-all
Show application help options. Also refer to
.BR gnome-options "(7) and"
.BR gtk-options (7).

.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print version information.

.SH "AUTHORS"
.TP
\fBJean Br\('efort\fR <\&jean.brefort@normalesup.org\&>"
Program author.
.TP
\fBDaniel Leidert\fR <\&daniel.leidert@wgdd.de\&>"
Manpage author.

.SH "SEE ALSO"
